Here is the cleaned up text:

Case Feed streamlines the way you create, manage, and view cases. It includes case actions like creating case notes, logging calls, changing the case status, and communicating with customers in a Chatter feed. Case Feed displays important case events in chronological order.

Agents assigned to a Case Feed page layout see a page that looks similar to the screenshot. Highlights Panel—Provides an overview of the most important information about a case, such as contact information, case name, case description, status, priority, and case owner.

Feed and Detail Views—From the feed view, agents can easily switch to the case detail view to see more in-depth information and work with related lists. Publisher—Contains actions agents use to work with cases, such as Email, Case Note, and Change Status.

Articles Tool—Lets agents find Knowledge articles that can help them resolve cases, and then attach them to a case or email them to customers. Feed Filters—Helps agents quickly find specific information in the feed by limiting the feed items that appear.

Feed—Offers a chronological view of the case’s history. Follow Button and Followers List—Let agents follow the case so they’re notified in Chatter of updates to it, and let them see other followers.

Administrators can customize most aspects of Case Feed, including:

* Fields in the highlight panel
* Actions that appear and the fields they include
* Feed filters that are available and where on the page the list appears
* Width of the feed

Use actions to work with cases in Case Feed, use feed filters to see all updates of one type, and use related lists to complete tasks. The articles tool can be used to search for relevant articles, attach them to a case, and email them to customers.

The case detail page can be used to see and update detailed information about a case and work with related lists. The Experience action in the case feed is your default option for responding to customers on cases that originated from an Experience Cloud site or customer portal.
title: Optimizing Case Management with Salesforce Service Cloud
